UPDATE public.questions SET
  stimulus_text = 'The study found that in the early phases of the universe, the rate of expansion was much higher than it is now.  It is known as the inflationary period. During that period, the universe expanded to the size that it is today, in a very short time. This period is followed by a slower rate of expansion, which is still occurring today. Researchers note that the pattern described above remained consistent across repeated observations, suggesting the finding was not a one-time anomaly. They caution that local conditions can still vary, yet the overall relationship held in each documented case.',
